}

post {
  url: {{ai_url}}/agent
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "message": "And what was the total amount?",
    "userId": "{{customer_id}}"
  }
}

docs {
  ## Agent — Follow-up (Conversation Memory)

  Demonstrates multi-turn conversation memory.
  The agent stores every turn (user + assistant) keyed by `userId`.
  On subsequent requests with the **same userId**, the history is injected into the prompt so the LLM can answer follow-up questions without repeating context.

  ### How to use
  1. First send `Agent - Order Status` or `Agent - My Orders` with `userId = {{customer_id}}`
  2. Then send this request with the **same** `{{customer_id}}`
  3. The LLM will answer referencing the previous response

  ### Memory limits
  Up to **10 turns** (20 messages) per session are kept. Older messages are dropped automatically.

  ### Reset memory
  Change the `userId` to start a fresh conversation.
}
